      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse 4M, medium 9M, fine 20M cells). GCI for velocity-based QoIs is 3.2% on the fine mesh. GCI for hemolysis index is 8.7%, exceeding the 5% threshold. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profiles, outlet pressure, fluid temperature, blood analog rheology) documented with measurement uncertainty and matched to simulation inputs within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles and outlet pressures are well-characterized (±2%). Blood analog viscosity was measured at 37°C ±0.5°C. However, the hematocrit of the bovine blood analog drifted between 38–42% across test runs and was not tightly controlled to a single target value, introducing unquantified variability in hemolysis susceptibility. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel or validation uncertainty Uval) computed for all primary QoIs; comparison includes experimental uncertainty and numerical uncertainty in denominator.",
      "rationale": "Relative error computed for velocity magnitude and NIH at all 5 operating points. Experimental uncertainty incorporated for PIV data. Numerical uncertainty (GCI) included for velocity but not propagated into the NIH comparison metric due to high GCI. Formal Uval metric incomplete for hemolysis QoI. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs are the same physical quantities as COU QoIs (absolute NIH) or demonstrated surrogates with quantified fidelity mapping.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses NIH as the primary QoI, consistent with the COU requirement for absolute hemolysis prediction. However, the validation geometry is the FDA generic pump (simplified impeller), while the COU device is a proprietary centrifugal VAD with different blade geometry. The surrogate fidelity mapping is qualitative only. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
