      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrated equivalent to COU device parameters within quantified tolerances; any deviations bounded by sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic pump geometry; COU device geometry differs in impeller blade count and volute design. Geometric equivalency has not been formally assessed. Material property equivalency (blood analog vs. clinical blood) relies on viscosity matching only; viscoelastic effects not considered. No sensitivity analysis bounds the impact of geometric deviations on hemolysis predictions. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
